    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="10">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Shift bars not being removed must be kept in the neutral position or the interlock parts lock the
                    bars.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the three (3) sets of tension springs and balls from housing bores have not been removed,
                place the shifter housing on its side to remove them (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300781">Figure 81</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300781" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300781" filename="../figg13/G1300781.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 81. Remove Tension Springs and Balls From Housing Bores</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If equipped, remove the oil trough retaining bolts and oil trough (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300782">Figure 82</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300782" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300782" filename="../figg13/G1300782.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 82. Remove Oil Trough</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lay the assembly on a flat surface with the housing rear to the right (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300782">Figure 82</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">While removing the top yoke bar to the right, remove the two (2) shift blocks (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300783">Figure 83</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300783" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300783" filename="../figg13/G1300783.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 83. Remove Shift Blocks</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the shift yoke and shift block from the middle yoke bar. As the neutral notch in the
                bar clears the rear boss, remove the small interlock pin from the notch bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300784">Figure 84</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300784" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300784" filename="../figg13/G1300784.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 84. Remove Interlock Pin From Notch Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the actuating plunger from the center top bore boss (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300785">Figure 85</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300785" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300785" filename="../figg13/G1300785.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 85. Remove Actuating Plunger From Center Top Bore Boss</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two (2) shift yokes from the bottom yoke bar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300786">Figure 86</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300786" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300786" filename="../figg13/G1300786.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 86. Remove Shift Yokes From Bottom Yoke Bar</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">As the shift bar clears the last boss, two (2) 3/4 inch interlock balls drop from the bottom
                rear boss bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300787">Figure 87</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300787" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300787" filename="../figg13/G1300787.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 87. Remove Interlock Balls</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If damaged, remove the plug, spring and plunger from the 1st and reverse shift yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300788">Figure 88</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300788" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300788" filename="../figg13/G1300788.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 88. Remove Plug, Spring and Plunger From 1st and Reverse Shift Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the yoke or block parts and replace the worn parts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the yoke actuator parts are damaged, replace them (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300789">Figure 89</hotlnk>and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300790">Figure 90</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300789" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300789" filename="../figg13/G1300789.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 89. Inspect Yoke Actuator Parts</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1300790" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300790" filename="../figg13/G1300790.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 90. Inspect Yoke Actuator Parts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
